    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.5.0 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.0.5\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux: up to date: 13-09-21\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nsuckless st\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nst-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\npacman official repositories\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n* Add following keymap\r\n\r\n```\r\n {'t', '<c-n>', [[<c-\\><c-n>]], {}},\r\n```\r\n\r\n* Open neovim terminal\r\n* Execute the key combination in terminal insert mode\r\n\r\n### More information:\r\n* There is only one map by `<c-n>` is registered\r\n```\r\n:tmap <c-n>\r\nt  <C-N>         <C-\\><C-N>\r\n```\r\n\r\n* Just executing ` <C-\\><C-N>` will result in same behavior, how ever, If I remap the same action to any other key combination if works fine.\r\n\r\n* Just using <c-n> on the terminal will show the next command in the history.\r\n\r\n* I see the memory issue in Alacritty terminal as well.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/18459807/133034264-c94a4a0c-9362-4445-88a5-7ce6a3a15f75.mp4\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe mode should be switched to normal mode\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nNeovim freezes and will not react to any key presses after. The CPU and memory usage will increase until no memory left and freezes the OS.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
